                            <comment id="12984796" author="ruffiano" created="Fri, 21 Jan 2011 16:18:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Went through the same process to replicate the issue this time with HadoopNode99, which was also hosting the &lt;del&gt;META&lt;/del&gt; table.  Not 100% if that was the case last time as well, going to go out on a limb and assume it was, I&apos;ll go through the process again on a server not hosting root or meta later today.  Manually removed it from the DNS server and made sure /etc/hosts was clear of any references to it.  That alone didn&apos;t cause any issues, assuming references to it&apos;s IP are cached in &lt;del&gt;root&lt;/del&gt;.  Then I went ahead and gave EC2 the go ahead to kill the server.  Server still did it&apos;s normal shutdown process of stopping regionserver and datanode, then vanishing into the nothingness of the cloud.  Then I received the following angry logs, web UI deaths, as well as it still passing out the hadoopnode99 host to all client servers:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://pastebin.com/TjJcwqMq&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://pastebin.com/TjJcwqMq&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Again, to revive the master, I put a faulty entry in /etc/hosts and restarted the master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14067311" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 19 Jul 2014 01:04:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue wasn&apos;t actionable&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
